    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1921-04-28T15:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1921-04-28T15:00:00-05:00" n="59"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d59">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">462.00 R 29/713: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wallace</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-04-28T21:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 28, 1921—9 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received April 29—5:30 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>296. B–463. The Separation Commission in plenary session last night delivered the
                    following <hi rend="italic">note verbale</hi> to Von Oertzen of the German
                    Reparation Delegation at Paris:<note n="41" xml:id="d59fn41">This sentence
                        paraphrased.</note>
                    <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“Reparation Commission in pursuance of stipulations article 233 treaty
                            has decided unanimously to fix at 132 billion gold marks amount damages
                            reparation due by Germany under terms article 232 second paragraph and
                            of annex I of part VIII of the treaty. In fixing this amount Commission
                            has effected necessary deduction from amount of damages in order to make
                            allowance for the restitution effected or to be effected in execution
                            article 238 and in consequence no credit will be allowed Germany in
                            respect such restitutions. The Commission has not included in the above
                            amount sum in respect further obligations incumbent on Germany in virtue
                            of third paragraph article 232 to ‘make reimbursement of all sums which
                            Belgium has borrowed from Allied and Associated Governments up to
                            November 11th 1918, together with interest at the rate of 5 percent on
                            such sums.’”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <list>
                            <item>Logan</item>
                            <item>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Wallace</hi>
                            </item>
                        </list>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
